<p><cs><col><b>Mountain spinach</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Garden
orache</cref>, under <er>Orache</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>New Zealand
spinach</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a coarse herb (<spn>Tetragonia
expansa</spn>), a poor substitute for spinach.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Various other pot herbs are locally called
